### TITLE ###
No filter one option
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger"]
print(pick(opts))
### STDOUT ###
Hamburger

### TITLE ###
Filter with one option
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger"]
print(pick(opts, "burg"))
### STDOUT ###
Hamburger

### TITLE ###
Filter to one option
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger", "Chicken Burger", "Sandwich", "Fish", "Chickwich"]
print(pick(opts, "Hamb"))
### STDOUT ###
Hamburger

### TITLE ###
Errors if empty options
### INPUT ###
opts = []
pick(opts)
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20000]: Filtered 0 options to 0 with filters: []
  --> <script>:2:1
  |
1 | opts = []
2 | pick(opts)
  | ^^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad explain RAD20000


### EXIT ###
1
### TITLE ###
Errors if filtered to zero options
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger", "Chicken Burger", "Sandwich", "Fish", "Chickwich"]
pick(opts, "asdasdasd")
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20000]: Filtered 5 options to 0 with filters: [asdasdasd]
  --> <script>:2:1
  |
1 | opts = ["Hamburger", "Chicken Burger", "Sandwich", "Fish", "Chickwich"]
2 | pick(opts, "asdasdasd")
  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad explain RAD20000


### EXIT ###
1
### TITLE ###
Works with multiple tokens
### INPUT ###
filter = ["Ham", "ger"]
opts = ["Hamburger", "Chicken Burger", "Sandwich", "Fish", "Chickwich"]
print(pick(opts, filter))
### STDOUT ###
Hamburger

### TITLE ###
Interactive navigate and select
### DESCRIPTION ###
Multiple options remain, so the interactive picker runs. Arrow down moves the
cursor to the second option, Enter selects it. Frames capture each render.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger", "Pizza", "Sushi"]
print(pick(opts))
### KEYS ###
down
enter
### STDOUT ###
Pizza

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Pick an option
> Hamburger
  Pizza
  Sushi
--- frame 1 (down) ---
Pick an option
  Hamburger
> Pizza
  Sushi
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
Pick an option Pizza
### TITLE ###
Interactive filter then select
### DESCRIPTION ###
Typing narrows the list live (fuzzy match), then Enter selects the remaining
match.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger", "Pizza", "Sushi", "Salad"]
print(pick(opts))
### KEYS ###
"sa"
enter
### STDOUT ###
Salad

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Pick an option
> Hamburger
  Pizza
  Sushi
  Salad
--- frame 1 (s) ---
Pick an option
/s
> Sushi
  Salad
--- frame 2 (a) ---
Pick an option
/sa
> Salad
--- frame 3 (enter) ---
Pick an option Salad
### TITLE ###
Interactive cancel
### DESCRIPTION ###
Ctrl-C aborts the picker, which surfaces as a rad error and a non-zero exit. No
summary frame is left behind on cancel.
### INPUT ###
opts = ["Hamburger", "Pizza", "Sushi"]
print(pick(opts))
### KEYS ###
down
ctrl-c
### STDERR ###
error[RAD20000]: pick canceled
  --> <script>:2:7
  |
1 | opts = ["Hamburger", "Pizza", "Sushi"]
2 | print(pick(opts))
  |       ^^^^^^^^^^
  |
   = info: rad explain RAD20000


### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Pick an option
> Hamburger
  Pizza
  Sushi
--- frame 1 (down) ---
Pick an option
  Hamburger
> Pizza
  Sushi
### EXIT ###
1
